This paper discusses the Nystrom method for large-scale statistical learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and data science. Specifically, the paper focuses on kernel SVMs, which are commonly used in areas such as computer vision and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
